[How to build in-tree CONFIG virtual/kernel]
Being in-tree means there is a CONFIG_XXX entry in .config or defconfig.  Drivers like TPLink Wireless 8821au are not in-tree modules.  Drivers such as USB-Serial-Converters are in-tree modules.
The following describes the procedure to include the PL2303 driver for the shutter controller USB convertable cable.
# bitbake -c cleansstate imx-image-full
bitbake -c cleansstate virtual/kernel # must-do before menuconfig

bitbake -c menuconfig virtual/kernel
1. Set CONFIG_USB_SERIAL_PL2303=y
2. Set CONFIG_ADVANCED_ROUTER=y
   (implicitly CONFIG_IP_MULTIPLE_TABLES=y)
That is: Set
    Device Drivers | USB support | USB Serial Converter support | USB Prolific 2303 Single Port Serial Driver = Y
    Networking support | Network options | TCP/IP networking | IP: advanced router = Y

bitbake -c savedefconfig virtual/kernel
1. cp -p ~/adv-release-bsp/3720a2/tmp/work/imx8mprsb3720a2-poky-linux/linux-imx/6.1.22+gitAUTOINC+2a654b377a-r0/build/defconfig  ~/adv-release-bsp/sources/meta-tglobal/recipes-kernel/linux-imx/myDefconfig
2. vi linux-imx_%.bbappend
     SRC_URI += file://myDefconfig

bitbake -c cleansstate virtual/kernel
# time bitbake virtual/kernel (~6)
time bitbake imx-image-full (!12min)

